{"lemma":"مَسْكَنٌ","slug":"مَسْكَنٌ","root":"س.ك.ن","root_slug":"س-ك-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/س-ك-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مَسْكَن","root":"سكن","pos":"N","occurrence_count":12},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":6},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n20276"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D9%83%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"noun of place of سَكَنَ (sakana): residence; house, home"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"dormitory"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"active participle of سَكَّنَ (sakkana)","tags":["active","form-of","participle"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"soothing, calming"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"analgesic"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"analgesic, painkiller"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Noun of place from the verb سَكَنَ (sakana, “to reside”). Cognate with Hebrew מִשְׁכָּן (miškān, “dwelling”) and Classical Syriac ܡܫܟܢܐ (meškānā).\n\nDerived from the active participle of سَكَّنَ (sakkana, “to soothe”)."},"ipa":["/mas.kan/","/mu.sak.kin/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n20276","headword_ar":"مَسْكَنٌ","root":"skn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokinN","text_ar":"مَسْكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, L, Msb, K;) the people of El-Hijáz say the former, (S, L,) and the latter is anomalous; (L;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of habitation;"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a place of alighting, abiding, sojourning,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lodging; an abode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a dwelling;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a house,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tent;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, Msb;) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masaAkinu","text_ar":"مَسَاكِنُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanu","text_ar":"سَكَنُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies the same as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokinN","text_ar":"مَسْكِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", [thus in the"},{"kind":"page_break","n":1395},{"kind":"text","text":"Kur xvi. 82,] (Lh, L, and Ham p. 400,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Lh, L,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonN","text_ar":"سُكْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArN fiyhaA","text_ar":"دَارٌ فِيهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonN","text_ar":"سُكْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokanN","text_ar":"مَسْكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A house in which is a place of habitation,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a lodging"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (L: [↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonN","text_ar":"سُكْنٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are there mentioned as syn., each of them, with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"masokanN","text_ar":"مَسْكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", but in different places; and I incline to think that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonN","text_ar":"سُكْنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"thus mentioned may be a mistranscription for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sakanN","text_ar":"سَكَنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": I have not found it elsewhere in this sense:]) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAriY laka sukonaY","text_ar":"دَارِى لَكَ سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", in which the last word is [said to be] virtually in the accus. case, as a denotative of state, meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"My house is for thee,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as made"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"given"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to be inhabited,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as being inhabited:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"laka daAriY h`*ihi sukonaY","text_ar":"لَكَ دَارِى هٰذِهِ سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To thee this my house is a lent dwelling-place:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmaroA^api","text_ar":"المَرْاَةِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sukonaY","text_ar":"سُكْنَى","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The wife's dwelling-place in which the husband lodges her."},{"kind":"text","text":"(L.)"}],"source_refs":["S","L","Msb","Lh","Mgh"]}]},"classical_definitions":{"source":"hawramani","url":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/%D9%85%D8%B3%D9%83%D9%86/","headword_ar":"مسكن","entries":[{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_1","lexicon_en":"Ibn Manẓūr, Lisān al-ʿArab (d. 1311 CE)","lexicon_ar":"لسان العرب لابن منظور","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=4360#8491cc","body_html":"<p>مسكن: جاء في الخبر: أَنه نهى عن بيع المُسْكانِ، روي عن أَبي عمرو أَنه</p><p>قال: المَساكِين العَرَابين، واحدها مُسْكان. والمَساكِين: الأَذلاَّء</p><p>المقهورون، وإن كانوا أَغنياء.</p>"},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_32","lexicon_en":"Supplément aux dictionnaires arabes by Reinhart Dozy (d. 1883 CE)","lexicon_ar":"تكملة المعاجم العربية لرينهارت دوزي","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=4360#a237f0","body_html":"مسكن: مسكن: انظرها عند فوك في مادة ( miser) أي (مسكين، تعيس، حزين).<br>مسكن: أعطى على مضض، عن كراهة (الكالا) (وبالأسبانية escatimar) : أي بخل، شح (انظر فكتور).<br>مسكن: استكان وتذلل ل ... (بوشر)."},{"lexicon_id":"dictionary_21","lexicon_en":"Muḥammad al-Fattinī, Majmaʿ Biḥār al-Anwār fī Gharāʾib al-Tanzīl wa Laṭāʾif al-Akhbār (d. 1578 CE)","lexicon_ar":"مجمع بحار الأنوار للفَتِّنيّ","permalink":"https://arabiclexicon.hawramani.com/?p=4360#11bc8b","body_html":"<span class=\"title1\">[مسكن]</span><span> ط: فيه: أحيني \"مسكينا\"، هي من المسكنة وهي الذلة والافتقار، أراد إظهار تواضعه وافتقاره إلى ربه إرشادًا لأمته للتواضع. نه: فيه \"مسكن\"- بفتح ميم وكسر كاف: صقع بالعراق وموضع بدجيل الأهواز حيث كانت وقعة الحجاج وابن الأشعث.</span>"}]}}